For a natural transformation η : F ⇒ G between functors F, G : C ⥤ D, the naturality square is the commutative square associated to every morphism f : X → Y in C.
It is
F(X) --F(f)--> F(Y)
 |              |
η_X            η_Y
 |              |
v              v
G(X) --G(f)--> G(Y).
Commutativity means G(f) ∘ η_X = η_Y ∘ F(f).
